# ASP.NET Core Web App – Project Structure

## Overview

This project was created using the **ASP.NET Core CLI**.
The purpose of this project is to understand the basic structure of an ASP.NET Core web application and how different components work together.

---

## Creating the Project

The project was created using the following command:

```
dotnet new webapp -n MyWebApp
cd MyWebApp
dotnet run
```

After running the application, the web server starts and the application can be accessed through the browser using:

```
https://localhost:5001
```

---

## Project Folder Structure

```
MyWebApp
│
├── Pages
│   ├── Index.cshtml
│   ├── Privacy.cshtml
│   └── Shared
│
├── wwwroot
│   ├── css
│   ├── js
│   └── images
│
├── appsettings.json
├── Program.cs
├── MyWebApp.csproj
└── README.md

1. Program.cs

This is the entry point of the application.


2. Pages Folder

This folder contains Razor Pages, which define the UI of the application.

Index.cshtml → Home page

Privacy.cshtml → Privacy page


3. wwwroot Folder

This folder contains static files used by the web application.

Examples:

CSS files for styling

JavaScript files for functionality

Images and other static resources


4. appsettings.json

This file stores configuration settings such as logging configuration and connection strings.


5. .csproj File

The .csproj file defines the project configuration, including:

Target .NET framework

Dependencies

Build settings



